org.sql: SELECT 1 AS one FROM projects LEFT OUTER JOIN members ON projects.id = members.project_id AND members.user_id = 529 AND projects.active = True LEFT OUTER JOIN member_roles ON members.id = member_roles.member_id LEFT OUTER JOIN roles AS assigned_roles ON 1 = 1 AND projects.active = True AND (assigned_roles.id = member_roles.role_id OR projects.public = True AND assigned_roles.builtin = 2 AND member_roles.id IS NULL) WHERE projects.lft >= NULL AND projects.lft < NULL AND projects.id <> 8184 AND assigned_roles.id IS NOT NULL LIMIT 1
